        "text_ahKGbw": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>A few gentle habits help this skin type as much as any single product does.<br/><br/>Moisturise while the skin is still slightly damp, which helps trap the water in. Wash with lukewarm rather than hot water, and something mild rather than a stripping, heavily foaming cleanser, since hot water and harsh soap pull out the very oils dry skin is short of in the first place. Try not to over-wash. Shelter the skin from cold wind and drying central heating. And be consistent, because dry skin responds far better to steady daily care than to the occasional heavy treatment.<br/><br/>You'll have noticed we never use synthetic fragrance. There's a single essential oil in the range, <a href=\"/blogs/ingredients/vetiver-vetiveria-zizanioides-root-oil\" title=\"Vetiveria Zizanoides (Vetiver) Root Oil\">vetiver</a>, at a low level and chosen on purpose, and it appears on every label so you can see exactly how much is there.</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "rte",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "text_color": "",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_iiUCEX": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Your skin can settle over time</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "h3",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "text_color": "",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_hVYV6M": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Dry isn't a fixed label. Cared for consistently, dry skin often gets better at holding moisture over time, and for some people it gradually settles toward the steadier Balanced type, where the daily upkeep gets easier. It's gradual, it comes from steady care rather than from any single product working magic, and it's a good reason to treat where your skin is today as a starting point rather than a verdict. If it changes, the skin type finder is always there to place yourself again.</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "rte",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
